sic, girls and the like?’ Father Frank was nearly pleading now.‘Fiction,’ sighed Andy. ‘Mirages in the desert of life, to make people feel like it might be worth it.’ ‘Oh,’ said Father Frank. ‘Oh I see, and do all you youngsters get this feeling?’‘Yes, I think so,’ said Andy, not even asking anyone else for their opinion, but most of us learn to live with it.’‘Well that’s a relief, I suppose.', 15743, 0), (340909, 'Each moment passes by and we do not even realize this. What we ought to cherish, we actually perish!', 11739, 0), (340910, 'If you want to move on, you actually have to make the decision to move on. It won''t happen automatically. You have to say, "I deserve better than this and no longer am I going to let this get the better of me", and then take the necessary action to move on with your life.', 12100, 0), (340911, 'Get some sleep. Our troubles will still be there on the morrow', 7171, 0), (340912, 'Life has simply decided to open the floodgates, trying to drown me in a whirlwind of twists and turns.', 3246, 0), (340913, 'A challenging life isn''t impossible to overcome, but it does mean that you might have to work a little harder to overcome it.', 12100, 0), (340914, 'No, you listen! All my life, you''ve told me that the world is a dark, cruel place. But now I see that the only thing dark and cruel about it is people like you!', 55576, 0), (340915, 'It was too long ago; she couldn’t recall the feelings of love, only remember that she’d had them. A dried-out memory, like a flower pressed between the pages of a book.', 55577, 0), (340916, 'If life is what you make it, the building blocks are your desire and your passion.', 9860, 0), (340917, 'Let''s go old school to impress people. Wear a smile, rather than a branded dress. Crease out our differences with understanding. And, use empathy, care, and patience as accessories. Then, let''s make a conversation, not talk. Ah, what a fine world it would be! Fine, pure and minus artifice.', 10254, 0), (340918, 'Life is a sage’s university', 55578, 0), (340919, 'No, the frigid, cold, empty thing that lives inside me showed up the day after my mother died. It told me it was pointless to care about people. It told me it was useless to consider what they think or feel or desire out of life.', 54023, 0), (340920, 'Destination is never a final one.Once you reach you plan for the next.', 31925, 0), (340921, 'The deepest and most profound wisdom that exists and moves through us is the intelligence of our own heart. It is a flowing sacredness. It can navigate you through anything. An intelligent ocean of life''s experience.﻿', 6164, 0), (340922, 'Nothing was more nauseating than people who constantly complained about their life, but did nothing about it.', 55579, 0), (340923, 'who accompany ignorants, lives in misery.', 47995, 0), (340924, 'Even when our Life is Full of Problems there will always be a Little bit sunshine of Happiness.', 12522, 0), (340925, 'A person with negative thoughts can never see the sunshine ( good things ) and feel the warmth ( happiness ) in their heart..', 12522, 0), (340926, 'All Knowledge is dangerous', 34193, 0), (340927, 'It was a kind of love where no matter what your relation with the person is, you care for them as much as you possibly can. Your protect them like parent, understand them like a sibling, talk to them like a friend and love them like a life-partner.', 49701, 0), (340928, 'Perhaps I should explain to him that it has been my particular way of frustrating time''s attrition, postponing death and sustaining the illusion that one can always erase everything and make a fresh start.', 55580, 0), (340929, 'Be Happy with what we Have Now in the Future it can change, but that is not Always to Better.', 12522, 0), (340930, 'As an adult, I know about life and death. I know that good people can die too soon and bad ones can live too long. I know that life''s not fair, and you take the bitter with the sweet and balance it all as best you can.', 31693,